hi guys! having issues with the batch archive functions in the v3 api - anyone else able to get requests through to that one right now? i'm getting http 400 replies with what seems to be a deserialisation error from hs ... would appreciate if anyone has a chance to fire a request from their end to try it out (as a proper external api client, not through the docs test api call thingy - that one works, but shows no details in the api call log in hs)

```{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Invalid input JSON on line 1, column 1: Cannot construct instance of `com.HubSpot.apiutils.core.models.batch.BatchInput$Json` (although at least one Creator exists): no String-argument constructor/factory method to deserialize from String value ('{\n  \"inputs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"19001\"\n    }\n  ]\n}')",
  "correlationId": "xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx"
}```

In case it helps anybody, associations seems to be the 3rd parameter;

```HubSpotClient.crm.deals.basicApi.getById(dealId, properties, associations, archived, idProperty);```
I have no idea if the others are then correct.
